    <h3 class="block w-full font-medium font-lg font-grey-800 mb-0.5">Attack Rolls</h3>
    <p class="block w-full font-grey-700 mb-2 font-xs">
        Used to see if the target is hit by the attack. Add 1d20 + modifier + proficiency bonus (if applicable). Results in success if greater than or equal to target's AC.
    </p>
    <h3 class="block w-full font-medium font-lg font-grey-800 mb-0.5">Damage Rolls</h3>
    <p class="block w-full font-grey-700 mb-2 font-xs">
        Used to calculate how much damage the target takes. Add damage dice + modifier + anything special (if applicable).
    </p>
    <h3 class="block w-full font-medium font-lg font-grey-800 mb-0.5">Spell Attack</h3>
    <p class="block w-full font-grey-700 mb-2 font-xs">
        Roll 1d20 + modifier + proficiency bonus (if applicable).
    </p>
    <h3 class="block w-full font-medium font-lg font-grey-800 mb-0.5">Spell Save</h3>
    <p class="block w-full font-grey-700 mb-2 font-xs">
        Target rolls defense and must beat the spell save DC.
    </p>
    <h3 class="block w-full font-medium font-lg font-grey-800 mb-0.5">Sneaking</h3>
    <p class="block w-full font-grey-700 mb-2 font-xs">
        Players roll against a target's passive perception. If the target is actively looking for the player use active perception.
    </p>
    <h3 class="block w-full font-medium font-lg font-grey-800 mb-0.5">Brawling</h3>
    <p class="block w-full font-grey-700 mb-2 font-xs">
        Both players start at 20 stamina. To hit roll 1d20, do not add modifiers or proficiency bonuses. Roll a 1d4 for damage. When stamina is reduced to 0 the player is winded and loses the brawl.
    </p>
